Next, we listen for interactions (i.e., messages that start with the command prefix) using the `on("interactionCreate")` event. If the command name matches the one we defined earlier ("ban"), we check if the member mentioned in the interaction options exists and is bannable (i.e., not a bot or a member with reduced privileges like an owner). If so, we kick them from the server and reply to the interaction with a success message. Otherwise, we inform the user that they need to mention the member they want to ban.
Finally, we log in to our Discord account using the `login()` method and start the bot.

